# Variables in SVG variables are not replaced

SVG supports variables, defined as:

```css
.something {
  --a-variable: value;
}
```
that can be used in the SVG definition:

```svg
<line ... stroke="var(--a-variable)" />
```

When defining re-usable objects, and re-using them with `<use ...>`, it's pretty much the only way to target the items inside the shadowed dom.

libsass does not replace the SCSS variable placed on lines beginning with "--".

